OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1776103864
OL,3,CDeer in Oxfordshire freed after
OL,4,Cbecoming entangled in rope
OL,6,FOne of the deer had already died
OL,7,Fbefore they were spotted.
OL,9,FMarie said that when they arrived, the
OL,10,Fsituation was both challenging and
OL,11,Fdistressing: "The surviving deer was
OL,12,Fclearly terrified, dragging the other,
OL,13,Fwhich had sadly already died, as their
OL,14,Fantlers were tangled together with
OL,15,Frope.
OL,17,F"It was a very difficult sight, and
OL,18,Fyou could see how stressful it was for
OL,19,Fhim, and I can only imagine how
OL,20,Fupsetting it must have been for the
OL,21,Fpasser-by who found them.
OL,26,@sD@NOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1776103864
OL,3,CDeer in Oxfordshire freed after
OL,4,Cbecoming entangled in rope
OL,6,F"Fortunately, I was able to lasso the
OL,7,Fbuck by his antlers and secure him to
OL,8,Fa tree, which allowed us to safely cut
OL,9,Faway the rope and free him.
OL,11,F"It was clear that we needed to act
OL,12,Fcarefully and quickly to save him.
OL,13,FDeer are particularly susceptible to
OL,14,Fstress and, in many cases, tragically
OL,15,Fdo not survive for very long after
OL,16,Fbeing trapped due to stress-induced
OL,17,Fmuscle breakdown.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1776103864
OL,3,CDeer in Oxfordshire freed after
OL,4,Cbecoming entangled in rope
OL,6,F"Sadly, in some cases, it is kinder
OL,7,Fand the best option for their welfare
OL,8,Fto put them to sleep to prevent the
OL,9,Frisk of a painful death hours later.
OL,10,FHowever, following a thorough
OL,11,Fassessment, we were delighted to be
OL,12,Fable to release the deer back to the
OL,13,Fwild."
OL,15,FThe RSPCA is reminding the public of
OL,16,Fthe dangers that discarded rope,
OL,17,Fnetting, and similar materials can
OL,18,Fpose to wildlife.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1776103864
OL,3,CDeer in Oxfordshire freed after
OL,4,Cbecoming entangled in rope
OL,6,FMarie added: "This is a stark reminder
OL,7,Fas to the risks that many outdoor
OL,8,Fobjects - such as rope and netting -
OL,9,Fcan pose to wildlife. It's sadly
OL,10,Fcommon for male deer to have their
OL,11,Fantlers tangled up, so it's vital that
OL,12,Fsuch materials are properly removed
OL,13,Fafter use, to prevent this from
OL,14,Fhappening.
OL,16,FFor more information about what to do
OL,17,Fif you find a deer in trouble, visit
OL,18,Fhttps://www.rspca.org. uk/
OL,19,Fadviceandwelfare/wildlife/ deer.
OL,26,@nD@NOU
